line_1: 'But you resolve to hide no Pelf,
line_2: 'And choose to walk abroad yourself:

line_1: Who has more grace than pelf,
line_2: Lord take him to thyself.

line_1: Is so like a miser when hoarding his pelf.
line_2: Unbending austerity, wrapt up in self,

line_1: Without enjoyment, covetous of pelf,
line_2: Tiresome to friends, and tiresome to himself,

line_1: CAnst Thou in Dungeons smother up that Pelf
line_2: That's dearer to thee than thy Self?

line_1: He, sir, is proof to grandeur, pride, or pelf,
line_2: And (greater still) is master of himself:

line_1: May I ne'er heave a sigh for dirty pelf,
line_2: Or any thing that but concerns myself,

line_1: Here I liv'd like a king, never hoarded my pelf,
line_2: Kept a coach for my sisters, a nag for myself,

line_1: Soldiers their same, misers forget their pelf,
line_2: The rake his mistress, and the fop himself,

line_1: Me neither pow'r shall tempt, nor thirst of pelf,
line_2: To flatter others, or deny myself,

line_1: The miser hates, unless he steals your pelf;
line_2: The prodigal, unless you rob yourself;

line_1: Of grandeur vain and fond of pelf,
line_2: 'Tis plain, my lord, you knew yourself.

line_1: " They cannot eat your pelf:
line_2: " They may devour yourself.

line_1: Nor, draining wasted realms for sordid pelf,
line_2: O scepter'd suicide! destroy thy self.

line_1: Whate'er the Passion, Knowledge, Fame, or Pelf,
line_2: Not one will change his Neighbour with himself.

line_1: For smuggled Honours, and ill-gotten pelf;
line_2: A Bard owes all to Nature, and Himself.

line_1: The group so bent on play and pelf,
line_2: VENUS might call her doves herself.

line_1: A Citizen of mighty Pelf,
line_2: But much a Blockhead, in himself

line_1: I'd gladly part with worldly pelf
line_2: The wilding rose, sweet as thyself,

line_1: Give some display of worldly pelf,
line_2: With pewter trenchers, on the shelf,

line_1: Avarice, repining o'er his pelf,
line_2: Mean Cunning, lover of himself;
